'''Grafeneck''' is a small rural village in [[Germany]], near the town of [[MÃ¼nsingen, Germany|MÃ¼nsingen]], south-west of [[Stuttgart]]. [[Grafeneck Castle]], which had previously been an asylum for crippled people, was turned by the [[Nazism|Nazis]] into an extermination facility.

Between January and December 1940, 10,654 people with mental disabilities or psychological disorders were gassed at this facility with [[carbon monoxide]] in the first [[gas chamber]] and then cremated. This was the beginning of the [[T-4 Euthanasia Program]].

